				"source": [
					"For this logic to work, the silver layer has to be registered in the Lake DB, should be straight-forward to amend existing code. The registration does not incur any extra cost\r\n",
					"\r\n",
					"Alternatively, instead of getting the transformation logic from a .sql physical file, you could store it in a Azure SQL Server table or physical file, and parse the transformation logic as a parameter in ADF using Lookup activity"
				]
			},
